                <p>Borderlands 4 launched on September 12 and it had a massive debut on Steam, eclipsing more than <a href="https://steamdb.info/app/1285190/charts/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">300,000 concurrent users</a>. The PC edition hasn't been without its issues, though, as players have complained about a range of technical and performance-related problems. Gearbox boss Randy Pitchford has chimed in as well with a <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/borderlands-4-boss-calls-people-4k-stubborn-disputes-reports-of-performance-issues/1100-6534746/" data-ref-id="1100-6534746">string of controversial posts on the subject.</a></p><p>Some of the issues are significant enough that Gearbox has already released updates that aimed to improve stability and improvements, while another update is coming today, September 18. "This is our top priority," the <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/news/app/1285190/view/534361794856091855" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">developer said</a> about addressing the PC issues. The exact contents of the second major PC update have not been announced, however.</p>



    
